bhutan, locals come up and talk to you, and you have a chance to soak up the settings at your on pace, not that of a rushed driver. see bhutan by bike tour talk[edit] common languages the 19 or so dialects and languages of bhutan can be divided into 4 major language groups (almost same): group 1. west: dzongkha of western bhutan & che-cha-nga-cha of south lhuentse and parts of mongar and trashiyangtse; group 2. south: lhotsamkha (nepali) of southern bhutan; group 3. east: scharchop (tsangla) of eastern bhutan; group 4. central: bumthangpa, mangdip (trongsa), au-gayma-la(of north lhuentse), khengkha (zhemgang 